		The deck used to play Spades is the same as a standard deck of cards except the 2 of hearts and
		the 2 of diamonds are taken out and replaced by the jokers. In many decks of cards one joker 
		has color and one does not. In spades the joker with color is known as the “big joker” while
		the joker without color is known as the “little joker.” If the jokers are identical it is up
		to the players to define which joker is the big and which is the little, the two must be visually
		different.
		</p>

